help.usercode: simple code of substances to be used for publication (ex: 01, 02…)
help.reference: code of substances, same name of txt file containing spectrum data
help.name: entire chemical name of substances
help.concentration: concentration in g/L for spectra acquisition
help.Mw: molecualr mass in g/mol of substance
help.pstart: position of the beginning of peaks
help.pstop: position of the end of peaks
help.isbase: 32768x1 logical vector (true if I is associated to baseline)
help.In: 32768x1 normalized intensity and average baseline value is 0 (I/trapz(ppm,I²))
help.In0: 32768x1 as In but centered on its average
help.gates: nx4 array, data generated for positioning gates, used with MULTIPB function
help.multiplicity: mulitplet in nmr spectra of substance
help.weight: nx1 array of weight attributed by user
help.weightn: nx1 array of normalized weight attributed by user (weight/sum(weight)
help.H: nx1 cell of proton number associated
help.Hn: nx1 cell of normalized proton number associated
help.normvalue: value to be used to normalize raw intensity

help.mulitplettypes: {sd.t.q.p.dd.tt.mr.mnr};s tructure (np (number of ROI) x 2 (2 fitting models)) with following fields
help.ngaussian: number of gaussian peaks found in considered ROI
help.ppm: chemical shift corresponding to this considered ROI
help.Iraw: intensity corresponding to this considered ROI
help.Irawn: normalized raw intensity by number of proton of molecule
help.Ifitn: normalized fitted intensity by number of proton of molecule
help.weight: weight of eah gaussian peaks (ngaussian x 1)
help.width: width of peak in ppm unit
help.position: position (center) of peak in ppm unit
help.window: structure with following fields : i) center: center of window ; ii) width: width of window (x(end)-x(1)) ; iii) widthapha: width of window calculated with alpha ; iv) alpha: probability of rejection in window (default=005) ; v) significantproba: percentage to keep significant peaks (95%); vi) nsignificantpeaks: number of significant peaks corresponding
help.multipletpresent: multiplet types present in substance spectrum
help.count: number of multiplets in each multiplet type (same order of multipletpresent)
help.all: all data concerning all multiplets of substance
